Via: New York Times 22 Oct 2001 [edited
<http://nytimes.com/aponline/national/AP-Anthrax-Glance.html>

Anthrax Cases and Exposures
---------------------------------
The 10 people who have contracted anthrax, others who tested positive
for exposure to anthrax and locations where anthrax was found. Some
findings are tentative; tests on other people are pending.
CONTRACTED INHALATION ANTHRAX:
-- [Male 63, photo editor, the Sun, American Media Inc., Boca Raton,
Florida. Died 5 Oct 2001
-- [Male 73, mail room worker at American Media Inc., Boca Raton,
Florida; remains hospitalized.
-- [Male 57, Washington DC postal worker. Hospitalized in serious
but stable condition in northern Virginia.
-- Second Washington DC postal worker. Hospitalized in Virginia.
In addition, tests are under way on 2 other Washington DC postal
workers who died of symptoms consistent with anthrax.
CONTRACTED SKIN ANTHRAX:
New York
------------
-- [Female 38, assistant to NBC anchor Tom Brokaw, New York; treated
with antibiotics.
-- Seven-month-old son of ABC News producer, New York; treated with
antibiotics.
-- [Female 27, assistant to CBS anchor Dan Rather, New York; treated
with antibiotics.
-- [Female 30, assistant to editorial page editor at New York Post
[New York;
treated with antibiotics.
New Jersey
--------------
-- Female letter carrier at West Trenton post office, Ewing, New
Jersey; treated with antibiotics.
-- [Male. 35 postal worker who sorts and loads mail at mail center in
Hamilton, New Jersey; treated with antibiotics.

TESTED POSITIVE FOR EXPOSURE:
-- Florida: 6 American Media employees; treated with antibiotics.
-- New York: 2 lab technicians, one policeman who worked on NBC case;
treated with antibiotics.
-- Washington DC: 28 people at the Capitol complex including aides to
Sen. Tom Daschle and 2 Capitol police officers; treated with
antibiotics.
LOCATIONS WHERE ANTHRAX FOUND:
Florida
---------
-- American Media Inc., Boca Raton, Florida, on keyboard of man who
died and in mail room.
-- 3 U.S. Postal Service facilities, two in Boca Raton, Florida, where
AMI is based; one in Lake Worth, near AMI's former address in Lantana.
New York
------------
-- NBC, New York, on letter postmarked 18 Sep 2001, Trenton, New
Jersey
-- Gov. George Pataki's office, New York City.
Washington DC
--------------------
-- Daschle's Washington office in the Hart Senate office building, on
letter postmarked 9 Oct 2001, Trenton, New Jersey
-- Dirksen Senate office building, where mail for Senate offices is
processed; Ford House office building, where mail for House offices is
processed; and an off-site postal facility where all congressional
mail is processed.
--
